<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52c3af67-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1918"><num value="1918">§ 1918.</num><heading> District courts; fines, forfeitures and criminal proceedings</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id52c3af68-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1918/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> Costs shall be included in any judgment, order, or decree rendered against any person for the violation of an Act of Congress in which a civil fine or forfeiture of property is provided for.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id52c3af69-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1918/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> Whenever any conviction for any offense not capital is obtained in a district court, the court may order that the defendant pay the costs of prosecution.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id52c3af6a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/955">62 Stat. 955</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52c3af6b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52c3af6c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 822 (R.S. § 974).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
</notes>
